reviews.review_text: We enjoyed a delicious Wild Salmon Burger on Kits Day 2023 ~ appreciated that there was a Table & Chairs outside the store where you could sit to eat and enjoy.  One of our group vowed that she didnt like Salmon but she sure enjoyed this Salmon Burger and is now a convert.  The $15 cost was well worth it for a freshly grilled generous Salmon portion~ hope we get to enjoy the same next year!  A small favour ~ It would be nice to have the option of different types of Buns, besides a White Bun ~ thank you!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for sharing your positive experience with us and for taking the time to leave such a wonderful review. Were thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our Wild Salmon Burger on Kits Day 2023 and that it was a hit with your group, even converting a self-proclaimed non-salmon lover! Your feedback regarding the bun options is greatly appreciated, and well definitely take it into consideration for future events. Thank you again for your kind words and support.

reviews.review_text: Came into the store today after a few months, and was really pleasantly surprised. The display counters have been redone, the displays look far more appealing, and I was really happy to see fresh sockeye from Barclay Sound (it always seems to be previously frozen, which I dont mind as the price is a bit better). I need to go back and pick up some frozen shrimp. Love the selection in the frozen section. Keep up the great work!

I purchased a variety of fresh seafood and everything was very fresh and delicious. The owner was very knowledgeable and helpful, and the store was very open and clean. Today I purchased ingredients for a Westcoast seafood dinner (pictured, minus the sushi), and all my guests complimented the wonderful seafood.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Leya, I am thrilled your dinner worked out so well!  Thanks for the compliments and Im sure most of the success had to do with your preparations!  See you again soon :-)

reviews.review_text: This year we were late for canning Sockeye salmon.  After phoning several places and not having any success we stumbled on to 7 seas. Spoke with Stevie who said yes they had Sockeye. The price was quite reasonable. We got our Salmon. They dressed, cleaned and cut off the fins - ready for canning. The fish was fresh and the service was superb. They have many other varieties of fresh and frozen fish and sea food.  And sauces and spices. I also talked with Cato, the store manager and knowledgeable about their products. They are oceanwise. Highly recommend this place.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind review Subrata!

reviews.review_text: Our family appreciates the opportunity to walk 4th avenue to explore the many opportunities for shopping a wide variety of products and our experience buying seafood at 7seas Fish Market we are always pleased with our fish choices on our latest experience we purchased Sockeye Fillets for our dinner meal what a very tasty dinner experience we really look forward to our next fish buying adventure the staff are very welcoming and provide excellent service and provide quality answers to customer questions..
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Michael, we value your feedback and patronage!

reviews.review_text: Came to the store to pick up some poke bowls to eat on the beach. The poke was delicious and fresh. Good size portions too. I had their original Samurai Warrior poke. The sauce was spicy, delicious, and unique. Im recommending this to my friends in the neighborhood!!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Awesome Thanks for the feedback Cecillya! Im thrilled that you enjoyed your Poke Picnic at the beach!  See you soon :-)

reviews.review_text: This is about my preferred place to shop for fresh fish and seafood, beside a full selections of goodies.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Chef!  I hope your event was a hit (Im sure it was)!  See you soon!!

reviews.review_text: What a great store. Their staff are Uber helpful - they provide lots of information on different fish choices and are will to explain patiently to someone I would be tempted to slap (that being me  ) Seriously good job team.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for the honest review Peter! We appreciate you!!

reviews.review_text: First time at this store, heard about their specials for BCspot prawns and copper river salmon. It is a little out of the way for us but so glad we came. All the staff was so friendly and the young owner that was helping us is so knowledgeable and helpful. Everything looked clean and fresh. Nice to hear the same family had been in this business since the 80s. Another staff member highly recommended the salmon pate which is excellent :) we will be returning for sure.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks for stopping by Jacqueline! (and for the kind words!!) We look forward to seeing you soon.  Check out our new Ceviche and up and coming Hawaiian Poke = )

reviews.review_text: The team is wonderful at this little seafood market. Tons to choose from, and the poke is amazing. They are sticklers for freshness and will cut what you need on the spot. You will find a large selection of frozen products like, octopus, Dungeness crab, and even bone broth and soups. Love this little store. Pop in while you re in the area.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Melissa. See you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Candied salmon is so good, especially the maple one, and employees are soo friendly! I went to buy some candied salmon as a souvenir before flying home and the employee was so considerate to even wrap it up securely before my flight and recommending the best way to transport it. Ill definitely be back next time Im out there.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Olga! We look forward to seeing you again!!  Safe travels :-)

reviews.review_text: Got some smoked salmon for our Eggs Benedict. Delicious and available in smaller portions. Owner is very knowledgeable and happy to share best practices when it comes to fish preparation and recipes. Excellent fresh fish selection.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Christian! We appreciate you.

reviews.review_text: Holy moly! Was their poke ever good!!! I was a bit skeptical at first but was SO pleasantly surprised! It was FULL AND PACKED with flavour! This is definitely my new go-to poke place!! Also, can t forget about the phenomenal customer service!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Jenn - thank you so much , and Im so happy our bowl hit your high standards!  It was a pleasure to meet you. We hope to see you soon!

reviews.review_text: Man I love this place! The people here are so genuinely nice and always have great recommendations. The frozen crab stuffed salmon pinwheels are to die for. They even let me taste test an oyster while I was waiting. Really made my day today :)
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Alex, youre the man!  Try to eat an oyster a day for your daily recommended dose of zinc!  Its vital to good health!   Take care and see you soon :-)

reviews.review_text: Great family run.  Service was awesome and so was the fish
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks George! So happy you had a great experience all around!

reviews.review_text: I shop at this 7 seas located on 4th regulary for the past 8 months as I am a private chef working closeby this location. 7 seas offer a wide variety of fresh fish and seafood. I usually go there to get shrimps, mussels, and a couple of different fish. The staff are always friendly and helpful. I have worked with James a couple  years back when I was working in the restaurant industry, and he is very knowledgable, friendly and always tries his best to meet the customers requests to make them happy! Last week, he had recommended to me their Arctic Turbot. I had tried it for my client and personally for myself, and we were impressed by how beautiful, succelent and buttery Arctic Turbot fish was. Now I have to say that Arctic Turbot is my top favourite fish. I am looking forward to try upcoming new fish/seafood they will be bringing in the store.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your kind review Kat!

reviews.review_text: Great family owned and operated business! A staple in Kitsilano
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Bobby! Youre the man!

reviews.review_text: Your chowder is the absolute best I ve ever had, tying one that I had at Bodega Bay, CA, about 35 years ago. Been looking all this time for it s equal. I added a little milk and a sauteed spot prawn left over from last night. Btw your spot prawns are always excellent too!!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you Bill!  We really appreciate your kind words and patronage!  We will see you soon, Im sure! = )

reviews.review_text: Amazing fresh seafood. The oysters, housemade tartar sauce, and clam chowder are the best!

Just bought some fresh cod fillets, and the fish was amazing! Employees were very friendly. The display is looking a lot better, and the fish is excellent. Highly recommend 7Seas and their products, especially the salmon candy dip!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thanks Kate, we just made a fresh batch of salmon candy dip and clam chowder with wild sockeye salmon and halibut!

reviews.review_text: Tried their Poke bowl special. Delicious especially the KPop flavor! Must try if youre in the Kitsilano area.

reviews.review_text: I have finally found a seafood store that I trust for the consistently great quality. I appreciate the advice I receive when purchasing the seafood and I much prefer this shop to Finest At Sea. Worth the drive.

reviews.review_text: Helpful, knowledgeable & cheery staff ready to showcase the beautiful selection of seafood they have! Love coming here. Easy 5 stars
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much for the kind words Jeff!  Its a pleasure to serve you!

reviews.review_text: Only ever had great service here. The mussels are amazing. Very fresh. Very cheap. They discard the ones that are no good. They explain to you how they are a living creature..... I would never buy vacuum sealed ones at Costco! Great store,  friendly service.

Love this store. I live in Kitts and shop locally and 7seas is my seafood shop. I really enjoy the crab and salmon cakes as well as the wonderful customer service. Its has a wonderful section of fresh seafood and I really like the fact that they are part of the ocean wise program.  Ive have recommended this store to many of my friends   Thanks 7seas
Bought a whole rock cod for a dinner and it was great!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Were so glad you enjoyed! Thanks Linh!

reviews.review_text: I had such a great experience! The staff is super friendly and everything I ordered was great quality and TASTY! Must try the clam chowder! Cheers! Nickole

reviews.review_text: Store was only interested in taking orders but failed to fulfil them. Email announcements were inconsistent with the actual situation and wasted a 30 minute drive all the way to Kits and back home empty handed. Update: James (sorry!), the manager,  reached out and extended his apologies. Mechanical breakdowns do exist, so I just hope that there is clearer communicate for next time.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Jeffrey, Im sorry our boat hit a log and didnt allow us to fulfill your order for fresh BC spot prawns yesterday.  We did our best and are fulfilling orders today (1 day late) if you still want your spot prawns, feel free to come get them!  Wild fishing is not as consistent as farmed fish or other farmed proteins, and that makes it hard to predict outcomes.  Our humble apologies as we tried our hardest and we hope you give us another shot to fulfill your needs in the future.  Thanks for your time and the opportunity - James (not Steve)

reviews.review_text: Decent variety of fresh and frozen fish and friendly staff. They also offer a good rewards program for regular customers.

reviews.review_text: A small store which has a reasonable selection of the fish. However I was only able to find two types of fresh fish, everything else was previously frozen.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Illia, we have a much wider selection now (2 years late to replying to this review my apologies for that also).. We now have many fresh options including: - Fresh Char - Fresh Haddock - Fresh Cod - Fresh Steelhead Salmon/Trout - Fresh Sablefish - Fresh Kuterra Salmon - Fresh Rainbow Trout - Fresh Mediterranean Seabass - Fresh Mediterranean Seabream - Fresh Sole - Fresh Snapper - Fresh/Live shellfish Thanks! Hope to see you again soon!

reviews.review_text: Didnt hav much fresh,,lotsa frozen
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello itsme ovrdar, Most fresh fish goes out of season during the autumn and winter months. Looks forward to our almost fully fresh seafood case in the summer months!  If you came recently, you should have found fresh options for:  cod, halibut, char, salmon, steelhead, rockfish, sole, along with live mussels, clams, oysters, and many more!  Im sorry you didnt see those in the display case.

reviews.review_text: Came here to grab some squid for paella, I am not sure how old it was but it basically disintegrated into mush in the paella. It smelled ok, but who knows.  This place is expensive and questionable quality.
Dont think leaving 40 bones in a 1lb  piece of salmon is acceptable. The explanation is its processed in Richmond plant now so its ok. Dont think so
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Donna, this was a miscommuncation. Im sorry for your poor experience. Please be sure to ask for fish that is pin boned removed at any fish monger as fin fish almost always contains bones (excepting shark and sturgeon which has cartilage instead). Usually bones are all removed but admittedly, sometimes they are not based on manpower or coordination of inventory and supply options.

reviews.review_text: Bought supposedly fresh spring salmon here yesterday. When we got home the fish rather than being firm was mush with an  off  smell. This place should be AVOIDED. There are so many good place for fish in Vancouver. No reason they should be in business.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Stanley, Im sorry about your terrible experience back in 2020. Come try us again and speak to the new manager. Hell be happy to make sure you get the best seafood for your needs!

reviews.review_text: paid an arm and a leg for BC spot prawns here assured enthusiastically by the gentleman behind the counter that they were fresh and amazing. got them home to find half of them mushy and bordering on inedible.  not okay and I wont be back.  with so many fresh fish shops in Vancouver this kind of inconsistency is not appreciated.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi J P, Im so sorry to hear about your experience 2 years ago. Spot prawns are definitely a fickle creature. Hopefully youll give us another shot to earn back your trust!

reviews.review_text: Their seafood is gross. Super intense  fishy  smell. Went back to the store about my experience and brushed off. Definitely won t return.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Lars, Im so sorry to hear that. I do apologize for your negative experience and thank you for your honest feedback. That you should feel to leave a 1 star review and negative commentary , we really must have done something wrong.  I am so sorry about this. I would love to know more about your experience so I can work to make it better in the future. Sometimes these things happen though it is not okay!  We typically have a very strong rotation on our fresh options and perhaps something slipped through the cracks. Please feel free to call me (James) at the shop (604-732-8608, so we may discuss and for a chance to make things right. Kindest Regards, James

reviews.review_text: AWFUL. After many years of buying fish here, just pulled Black Cod out of the oven to find it was liquified - most likely spoiled from having got wet. Disgusting experience, having to do dinner triage on protein. Thanks Seven Seas for ruining our dinner and our evening. We wont be back.
I was there today at 6:15 and they turned me away saying they were closed. Just a heads up that they close earlier than 6:30.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Margaret, Im sorry for the confusion. I dont know what the hours were like before. We are currently open from 9:30am-6pm DAILY!
